message.content: Immersed in the Dicas Advertiser, was the Rev. Edwards. Now he put down his paper, folded it, and glanced idly out of the window. Looked again, eyes starting from his head. "God bless my immortal soul," he cried. "Never mind your immortal soul," said Morgan Thomas tartly. "Here we are traversing the heavens at the very moment when we should be running into Llanguicke bus station.
